-- Fiji Beats New Zealand to Win Hong Kong Sevens Rugby Tournament
-- B y   M a r c o   L u i
-- 2012-03-25T12:24:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-25/fiji-beats-new-zealand-to-win-hong-kong-sevens-rugby-tournament.html
Fiji won the  Hong Kong  Sevens rugby
tournament, beating  New Zealand  35-28 in the cup final today.  Samoa overcame Argentina to take the plate and Kenya was
victor over the U.S. in the final of the bowl competition.  The three-day event was sold out, with about 40,000 tickets
sold a day. The 37-year-old tournament is the largest on the
world circuit for sevens, a shortened version of 15-man rugby
union.   To contact the reporter on this story:
Marco Lui in Hong Kong at 
